{
  "bio": [
    "David Kong, who also goes by Kong Hon Kong, founded Kuala Lumpur-based Nirvana Asia in 1990 and took it public in Hong Kong in 2014.",
    "Asia's largest death-services provider by sales, it runs private cemeteries, columbarium facilities and funeral homes in Malaysia and Singapore.",
    "The company is looking to launch four new sites in Malaysia and one in Singapore.",
    "Kong took Nirvana Asia private in 2016 in a $1.1 billion deal with private equity firm CVC Capital Partners."
  ],
  "about": [
    "The third of ten children, Kong was born to a family of rubber tappers in Kuala Lipis in northern Malaysia."
  ]
}